title: Demons win in five sets
text: Share T he Du rango High School girls volleyball team found itself down early against Grand Junction on Friday at Durango High School for a 5A/4A Southwestern league match. Down 0-2 in sets, the Demons came back to beat the Tigers and win the whole match 22-25, 19-25, 25-17, 25-21 and 15-12. Durango (7-7, 1-4) didn’t let go of the game even though Grand Junction (7-8, 3-3) had all the momentum on its side. “Grand Junction is a very good team,” Durango head coach Colleen Vogt in a phone interview with The Durango Herald. “We played the same, but we believed we could do it. After winning the third set, it was so much fun,” Senior Addison Swift led the Demons with 36 assists, and senior Maddie Robertson added 14 kills. “After the third set, the offense started clicking and our defense was all over the floor,” said Vogt. “Tonight was a real team effort.” Senior Sarah Waller had 10 kills, junior Josie Surmeier had six blocks and senior Leah Stephens added four blocks for Durango. “Our junior varsity played great tonight, too,” said Vogt. “Our program is full of a bunch of wonderful kids, I’m proud to be their coach.” Durango takes on Grand Junction (3-11, 2-4) Central at 11:30 a.m. Saturday at Durango High School.
